Subject: State Ethics Commission - Mandatory SEI Filing Requirements for HWTF Commissioners
Importance: High



Attached for your information is the Board of Ethics' January 2009 one page mini-newsletter regarding the annual Statement of Economic Interest (SEI) filing deadline – April 15, 2009.   As Commission members appointed by the Governor, Senate Pro-Tem or Speaker of the House, you are obligated to file an annual SEI with the NC Board of Ethics.  By now, you should have received a notice in the mail from the State Ethics Commission about this annual filing requirement.



If you did not file in 2008 or have never filed because you are newly appointed to the Commission, then you’ll need to fill out the <http://www.doa.state.nc.us/ethics/form1.htm>Statement of Economic Interest (long form).  In 2009, individuals who previously filed an SEI in 2008 and remain in the same position will have the following options to comply with the annual SEI filing requirements:



1. File a 2009 “No-Change Form.” The 2009 No-Change Form is designed for filers who have had no changes to their personal or financial circumstances that would require an update to their 2008 SEI. That Form includes an optional Additional Disclosure Addendum on which filers may, but need not, disclose additional information to assist the SEC in advising the filer.  The form can be downloaded at <http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm>http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm.


1. File a 2009 “Amendment to SEI.” The Amendment to SEI is designed for filers who have had some changes to their personal or financial circumstances that require an update to the information provided on their most recently filed 2008 SEI, but who do not want to file a new “Long Form.” These filers need only respond to questions where they have had changes to their filing information. However, in the event you have any changes to your 2008 responses to a particular question, you must answer that question fully and completely, updating that information on the 2009 Amendment to SEI as of the time period identified in that question. For example, if during 2008 you sold securities that were previously disclosed or you bought securities in another company valued at $10,000 or more, you must respond to Question 5(a) on the 2009 Amendment to SEI in full by listing all securities owned as of 12/31/08. It is not sufficient to only list the names of securities purchased and sold. The Amendment to SEI also includes an optional disclosure addendum. Please see the instructions to the Amendment to SEI for additional information.  (FYI – The Amendment to SEI is only available to individuals who filed a complete SEI in 2008, please contact the State Ethics Commission at (919) 807-4620 or <mailto:ethics.commission@doa.nc.gov>ethics.commission@doa.nc.gov)


1. File a New 2009 SEI “Long Form.” Filers always have the option of filing a new SEI (the “Long Form”), responding to all 19 questions. A newly-filed Long Form will supersede and replace any previously-filed forms. This form can be downloaded at <http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm>http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm.


All forms are available electronically on the SEC’s website at <http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm>http://www.ethicscommission.nc.gov/secoi.htm.



You must mail or deliver your original, notarized form to the SEC no later than April 15, 2009 - Failure to comply may subject you to a $250 fine and disciplinary action, including removal from your public position.  Electronic or faxed SEIs will not be accepted. Please retain a copy for your records.



For any specific questions about forms or filing, please contact the State Ethics Commission at 919-807-4620.  For general questions, please feel free to call Kristal Kingi-Shearin, HWTF Administrative Officer at 919-855-6876.



