Dear Governor Perdue:



Congratulations on your historic inauguration as the chief executive of the state of North Carolina.  Also, thank you for the openness and the inclusiveness that has been exhibited to the citizens of our state during the early stages of your administration.



Right at the beginning of this letter, I want to establish that I have no desire to personally sit on the North Carolina Historical Commission. 



However, I am writing to suggest that your appointments to this important commission should allow for a much more inclusive reflection of the racial/ethnic mosaic of North Carolina.



