Here is the relevant language from the waiver document (top of Page 9 of 189):



The #0662 Comprehensive Waiver will offer adult participants the opportunity to choose their parents, guardian of the person or other family member to provide a daily service through a Home Supports service definition. Home Supports will be similar to Residential Supports which is provided in the group homes. Parents who reside with their adult child may only provide Home Supports. Alternative services, Home and Community Supports and Personal Care Services, will be provided by someone not living with the participant.

> NOTE BY MARY SHORT (1/13/09):  In the above paragraph, please be aware that Residential Supports is provided in GROUP HOMES.  Meaning, that the provider is paid for MORE THAN ONE individual to provide a 24-hour service to each individual.  Because Medicaid is billed for "1 unit" of service (24 hours equals 1 unit), a provider who has 4 residents can bill 4 units a day without violating Medicaid billing rules.  And that is necessary because a provider may take a resident to a medical doctor who is also going to bill Medicaid for "units" of services within that same 24-hour period.


A Technical Amendment (TA ... and there were four TA's to the previous waiver) would be quite simple: 



Parents who reside with their adult child may only provide Home Supports. Alternative services, Home and Community Supports and Personal Care Services, will be provided by someone not living with the participant.  However, parent(s) who reside with more than one adult child may provide Home Supports in the same manner as Residential Supports are provided in group homes OR alternative services of Home and Community Supports and Personal Care Services may be provided in conjunction with others not living with the participants.



All my suggested TA does is return these families to hourly services to be provided by either the parent(s) or other staff, related or unrelated, living with or not living with.  And as hourly services, any one person would not bill for more than 16 hours a day!  And as hourly services, any one person could work in any combination needed amongst all the CAP-MR/DD recipients in the home!



